						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Aggaparāju, 1008 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 930, Vaiśākha Puṇṇami, Friday</hi> corresponding <hi rend="bold">1008 A.D. April 23, Friday °14.</hi> There was a lunar eclipse on this day, not mentioned in the record. The cyclic year was Kīlaka.</p>						

						<p>Commences with the <hi rend="italic">Praśasti</hi> of Bāṇa king. <hi rend="italic">Sakalajagatrayābhivandita, Mahābalikulōdbhava</hi> etc., and records the gift of 24 <hi rend="italic">maruturs</hi> of land by the chief to the god, Agrastēśvara-Bhaṭāra of Annagūru for worship and offerings. Mentions Pedda-rājaya and Koṇḍuka-rājaya.</p>						

						</summary>
